⚙️ Hands-On Tasks – Day 3 (DevOps Beginner Series)
🔹 1. Linux User Data Transfer

Simulate transferring user data between directories.

# Create user data directory
mkdir -p /tmp/dev/user1

# Create sample file
touch /tmp/dev/user1/data.txt

# Create backup directory
mkdir -p /tmp/backup/

# Move data to backup
mv /tmp/dev/user1/data.txt /tmp/backup/
🔹 2. Secure Root SSH Access

Disable root login via SSH (security best practice).

# Open SSH configuration file
sudo vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config

# Find and update this line:
PermitRootLogin no
# Restart SSH service
sudo systemctl restart sshd
🔹 3. Data Backup for Developer

Create backup before deployment (rollback safety).

# Create backup directory
mkdir -p /backup

# Copy project data
cp -r /home/user/project /backup/

# Rename backup version
mv /backup/project /backup/project_v1
🎯 Goal
Practice safe file movement
Understand deletion risks
Learn real-world backup strategies

👉 These tasks simulate real DevOps operations used in production systems.
